01:08:22.320 --> 01:08:25.160
Is that exodus space dot com or what?

01:08:25.880 --> 01:08:27.440
Exodus propulsion dot space.

01:08:28.020 --> 01:08:29.740
Exodus propulsion dot space.

01:08:29.820 --> 01:08:30.700
OK, check that out.

01:08:30.700 --> 01:08:36.260
And you've shown your experiments with all of the configurations that would not all of them.

01:08:36.320 --> 01:08:38.520
OK, we have to keep some stuff quiet.

01:08:38.740 --> 01:08:39.900
OK, cool.

01:08:40.120 --> 01:08:48.420
So are you doing like lateral propeller experiments or are you doing things that involve like lifting objects?

01:08:48.900 --> 01:08:51.160
We're not lifting objects yet in Earth's gravity.

01:08:51.280 --> 01:08:53.340
OK, we're measuring the forces of these objects.

01:08:53.480 --> 01:08:53.720
Yeah.

01:08:54.300 --> 01:08:59.560
And seeing how much their force can lift as compared to Earth's gravity.

01:08:59.560 --> 01:09:00.320
Got it.

01:09:00.700 --> 01:09:04.680
So we do have thrusters that are theoretically capable to lift themselves up.

01:09:05.160 --> 01:09:08.020
The problem is all of the hardware that goes with it.

01:09:08.020 --> 01:09:13.100
The voltages and the powers and the wires and the framing and all that other stuff is not there yet.

01:09:13.260 --> 01:09:21.680
So you have to it's like saying your car engine can lift the engine, can move the engine down the street, but no tires and no frames.

01:09:21.840 --> 01:09:22.800
And it's not very useful.

01:09:22.800 --> 01:09:23.380
Sure.

01:09:24.120 --> 01:09:28.980
But for right now, for what we have for lunar applications, space applications, it's awesome.

01:09:29.120 --> 01:09:29.960
It would be fantastic.

01:09:30.180 --> 01:09:30.700
That's amazing.

01:09:30.780 --> 01:09:35.880
So in microgravity or no gravity environments, you'll get a ton of thrust.

01:09:35.960 --> 01:09:36.200
Sure.

01:09:36.620 --> 01:09:37.240
That's amazing.

01:09:37.240 --> 01:09:40.260
And you're seeing weight reduction.

01:09:40.560 --> 01:09:41.140
Is that right?

01:09:41.620 --> 01:09:46.460
Well, we were saying that, yeah, the weight reduction would be something we're seeing, not mass reduction.

01:09:46.720 --> 01:09:47.200
Be careful.

01:09:47.640 --> 01:09:47.880
OK.

01:09:48.020 --> 01:09:48.560
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:09:48.560 --> 01:09:51.060
No, I know that gets thrown around in the UFO world all the time.

01:09:51.160 --> 01:09:51.180
It does.

01:09:51.180 --> 01:09:54.100
You're like, wait, you're reducing the mass of the thing?

01:09:54.100 --> 01:09:55.760
It's definitely not negative mass.

01:09:56.180 --> 01:09:57.260
Yeah, yeah, yeah, right.

01:09:57.860 --> 01:09:59.820
But yes, we do those tests.

01:09:59.900 --> 01:10:00.460
We have videos.

01:10:00.740 --> 01:10:01.920
I can share some with you.

01:10:01.980 --> 01:10:02.300
Please.

01:10:02.540 --> 01:10:05.320
Where we put stuff on a scale and we turn it on.

01:10:05.380 --> 01:10:05.940
It gets lighter.

01:10:06.060 --> 01:10:06.640
You flip it over.

01:10:06.700 --> 01:10:07.140
It gets heavier.

01:10:07.300 --> 01:10:08.380
We are going through a peer review.

01:10:08.620 --> 01:10:09.380
OK, amazing.

01:10:09.560 --> 01:10:10.960
For our second patent.

01:10:11.280 --> 01:10:11.580
Oh, cool.

01:10:11.580 --> 01:10:14.240
The examiner's office is doing a thorough peer review.

01:10:14.600 --> 01:10:17.360
They're the ones going down that path.

01:10:17.740 --> 01:10:18.000
OK, great.

01:10:18.020 --> 01:10:21.200
Which is apparently equivalent to a scientific peer review.

01:10:21.340 --> 01:10:22.680
So that's what I've been told.

01:10:22.920 --> 01:10:23.220
Amazing.

01:10:23.220 --> 01:10:27.420
So they're reaching out to people that have done it, reaching out to people who have signed

01:10:27.420 --> 01:10:29.180
affidavits to say, yes, I've seen it.

01:10:29.320 --> 01:10:30.920
Yes, I've reproduced it, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

01:10:30.980 --> 01:10:32.280
So they're going through that process now.

01:10:32.500 --> 01:10:36.580
What inspired you to pursue kind of more exotic propulsion to begin with?

01:10:36.640 --> 01:10:39.680
Did you have any childhood experiences around this sort of stuff?

01:10:40.740 --> 01:10:41.100
Yes.

01:10:41.540 --> 01:10:42.140
Yes, I did.

01:10:44.380 --> 01:10:47.020
I've always had a fascination with UFOs.

01:10:47.080 --> 01:10:49.340
And I think it's been around a long time.

01:10:50.180 --> 01:10:51.500
Just, you know, strange phenomena.

01:10:51.500 --> 01:10:52.780
But I think it really hit home.

01:10:53.760 --> 01:10:57.300
I think it was 11 or 12 when we worked our haunted house.

01:10:57.380 --> 01:11:00.780
My dad would make haunted houses in our garage in New York.

01:11:00.880 --> 01:11:01.160
Really?

01:11:01.560 --> 01:11:02.680
What does that even mean?

01:11:02.800 --> 01:11:05.400
Make haunted houses in your garage?

01:11:05.400 --> 01:11:15.160
Built a haunted house for the hotel that he worked at, a giant holiday inn, I think it was, or Hilton in Connecticut.

01:11:15.500 --> 01:11:17.340
And it was a massive haunted house.

01:11:17.380 --> 01:11:18.900
And his job was to build the whole darn thing.

01:11:19.140 --> 01:11:19.900
So he liked that.

01:11:20.120 --> 01:11:21.780
So the next year we did it at our house.

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:26.380
And we charged people like 50 cents to get in and go through the haunted house.

01:11:26.380 --> 01:11:31.880
And it was probably, I think it was a 9 by 11 single car garage haunted house.

01:11:32.800 --> 01:11:34.000
And we made $1,100.

01:11:34.480 --> 01:11:35.340
That's how many people showed up.

01:11:35.360 --> 01:11:35.780
It was crazy.

01:11:36.140 --> 01:11:36.780
It was a lot of fun.

01:11:38.800 --> 01:11:42.180
But, you know, we had a haunted house and it would go on for several weeks.

01:11:42.180 --> 01:11:48.780
One night, while I was there working it, a whole bunch of cars came into the driveway.

01:11:49.760 --> 01:11:52.260
And I recognized one of the kids getting out of the car.

01:11:52.360 --> 01:11:53.580
He said, Charlie, go look, look at that.

01:11:54.140 --> 01:11:59.380
And he shows me, you know, we look up and there's these six bright white lights at the top of the trees.

01:11:59.500 --> 01:12:00.760
Just hanging over the trees.

01:12:00.840 --> 01:12:01.900
Just going over the road.

01:12:02.500 --> 01:12:04.240
Just not moving very fast.

01:12:04.380 --> 01:12:06.540
Just hanging, hanging out in formation.

01:12:07.240 --> 01:12:08.460
No sound, no wind, no nothing.

01:12:08.460 --> 01:12:12.060
And all these cars were following these lights for several days.

01:12:12.460 --> 01:12:14.280
This happened over the course of several days.

01:12:14.780 --> 01:12:18.320
Was this like a famous UFO wave or flap or something?

01:12:18.380 --> 01:12:18.900
It was.

01:12:18.940 --> 01:12:20.640
It was in the papers and all that jazz.

01:12:20.880 --> 01:12:22.340
Southeast New York in the mid-80s.

01:12:23.200 --> 01:12:24.300
It was a lot of fun.

01:12:25.240 --> 01:12:27.260
You know, I thought that was pretty cool.

01:12:27.580 --> 01:12:32.340
So I kind of like geared my career towards trying to understand some of that stuff.

01:12:32.420 --> 01:12:34.600
I just wanted to know what the heck that was.

01:12:34.600 --> 01:12:38.580
And it got me interested in physics, I think, in science in general.

01:12:38.660 --> 01:12:39.880
I was always interested in science.

01:12:40.740 --> 01:12:45.740
Did they look like orbs or were they part of a formation or do you think they were part of the same craft?

01:12:45.740 --> 01:12:47.480
I think they were different craft.

01:12:47.600 --> 01:12:49.900
I think they were just separate crafts.

01:12:50.200 --> 01:12:50.480
Wow.

01:12:50.540 --> 01:12:52.220
I didn't see a solid object or anything.

01:12:52.380 --> 01:12:54.540
And so this was for days at a time.

01:12:54.740 --> 01:12:54.960
And it was.

01:12:54.960 --> 01:12:55.440
Well, they would come every night.

01:12:55.520 --> 01:12:58.720
They'd come back and they'd be different parts of the city.

01:12:59.040 --> 01:13:01.200
I don't know what the heck they were doing or why they were there.

01:13:01.200 --> 01:13:03.640
But it was, it was pretty, pretty cool.

01:13:03.740 --> 01:13:04.200
Pretty wild.

01:13:04.340 --> 01:13:11.540
It was about the same time where somebody said they saw the men in black, which I thought was hysterical.

01:13:12.700 --> 01:13:13.060
Wild.

01:13:13.300 --> 01:13:17.440
Because I was, you know, we were trick-or-treating out with my friends and we ran into another group of friends.

01:13:17.640 --> 01:13:22.560
And that group of friends said, hey, these two weird guys showed up in these 1920s outfits.

01:13:22.560 --> 01:13:30.620
And they said, you know, if you see something weird, they said, just close your eyes and tell it to land.

01:13:31.160 --> 01:13:32.520
Do you guys know what the heck that means?

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:33.480
Wow.

01:13:33.760 --> 01:13:34.420
I knew what it was.

01:13:34.880 --> 01:13:36.100
I said, where are these guys?

01:13:36.260 --> 01:13:37.080
They're right over there.

01:13:37.320 --> 01:13:40.080
So we went running to go look for them, but I didn't find anybody.

01:13:40.160 --> 01:13:41.460
But you knew of the men in black.

01:13:41.460 --> 01:13:42.220
I knew the phenomena.

01:13:42.420 --> 01:13:45.600
No one knew where the men in black were in the 1980s, early 80s.

01:13:45.620 --> 01:13:48.420
I don't think that was a thing, but I like to study that stuff.

01:13:48.720 --> 01:13:50.940
So I knew who that was or what that was.

01:13:51.200 --> 01:13:51.940
That's fascinating.

01:13:51.940 --> 01:13:53.200
So I thought, oh, this is cool.

01:13:53.600 --> 01:13:55.920
How can we learn more about this UFO flap?

01:13:56.020 --> 01:14:01.360
Does it have kind of a name that it's been kind of preserved by or is there a way to search it?

01:14:01.840 --> 01:14:03.480
You could just look at Brewster, New York.

01:14:03.640 --> 01:14:04.440
Brewster, New York.

01:14:04.600 --> 01:14:04.880
Okay.

01:14:05.160 --> 01:14:07.900
Probably 86 or 85, somewhere in that range.

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:08.360
Wild.

01:14:09.080 --> 01:14:12.920
Newspapers and television almost weekly carried reports of the sightings.

01:14:15.160 --> 01:14:20.840
From different places throughout the area, eyewitnesses all reported seeing the same thing.

01:14:20.840 --> 01:14:24.100
I looked up and right over my head, virtually.

01:14:24.560 --> 01:14:25.400
It wasn't far off.

01:14:25.480 --> 01:14:26.820
It was right over my head and very still.

01:14:27.520 --> 01:14:30.420
It was a rim of lights in the shape of a triangle.

01:14:31.060 --> 01:14:32.640
It was just a tremendous object.

01:14:32.820 --> 01:14:37.800
It was anywhere from wingtip to wingtip, about 50 or 60 yards.

01:14:38.120 --> 01:14:40.520
These were very, very unusual lights.

01:14:40.940 --> 01:14:42.520
I've never seen anything like it in my life.

01:14:42.940 --> 01:14:45.400
And so I pulled my car over and I had to take a look.

01:14:45.400 --> 01:14:47.520
But it was in the paper.

01:14:47.640 --> 01:14:49.320
I remember that because it lasted several days.

01:14:50.160 --> 01:14:53.360
And you hinted to me that you had an even more surreal experience.

01:14:53.360 --> 01:14:54.720
Yeah, that was not a surreal experience.

01:14:54.840 --> 01:14:56.360
That was just me seeing some lights.

01:14:57.040 --> 01:14:58.180
Surreal for many people.

01:14:58.420 --> 01:14:59.620
Eh, just lights.

01:15:00.220 --> 01:15:01.800
It was lights, but yeah.

01:15:01.980 --> 01:15:08.100
I had a more intense experience, I would say, many years later.

01:15:08.100 --> 01:15:15.800
Um, my wife and I experienced this and, uh, this was, it was a pretty cool event now that

01:15:15.800 --> 01:15:20.920
it's over, a little terrifying at the time, but, uh, we, we live in Cocoa beach.

01:15:21.120 --> 01:15:24.760
So we went out to the beach one night, I would say nine 30, 10 o'clock at night.

01:15:25.620 --> 01:15:27.760
And, um, we're the only ones there.

01:15:28.320 --> 01:15:29.540
It's not uncommon though.

01:15:29.580 --> 01:15:34.020
Back then, this is maybe 10 years ago and, uh, maybe 12 years ago.

01:15:34.020 --> 01:15:40.020
Um, so we live close to the Patrick air force base, which is South of us.

01:15:40.920 --> 01:15:46.300
And, uh, so out on the ocean, maybe about three miles outside South of us in the ocean,

01:15:46.440 --> 01:15:47.460
I would say about three miles.

01:15:47.580 --> 01:15:51.740
We could kind of gauge how far things are apart because we're used to the, all the rivers

01:15:51.740 --> 01:15:52.760
and they're all three miles wide.

01:15:52.840 --> 01:15:54.260
So this is about three miles out of the ocean.

01:15:54.460 --> 01:15:58.060
We see a red light, just a beacon, just bleeping.

01:15:59.120 --> 01:15:59.700
No big deal.

01:15:59.940 --> 01:16:00.620
Just a boat.

01:16:02.320 --> 01:16:03.120
Thousands of boats.

01:16:03.120 --> 01:16:04.500
Thousands of boats, but not that night.

01:16:04.580 --> 01:16:09.440
There are now thousands of boats and, uh, it gets brighter and it gets brighter.

01:16:10.220 --> 01:16:12.460
We're like, man, that's, it's getting kind of bright.

01:16:12.940 --> 01:16:13.660
What is that?

01:16:14.080 --> 01:16:16.740
What, you know, beacons don't get that bright.

01:16:17.180 --> 01:16:17.980
So it's gotta be a boat.

01:16:18.180 --> 01:16:19.000
Maybe someone's in trouble.

01:16:20.160 --> 01:16:23.320
And then it gets really bright and then it explodes.

01:16:24.640 --> 01:16:29.420
So we see this giant, I don't want to say mushroom cloud, but it got very, very bright.

01:16:29.420 --> 01:16:34.880
So bright, it lit up the whole beach as far as the eye can see for, you know, all the way

01:16:34.880 --> 01:16:36.060
from Cape Canaveral, all the way down.

01:16:37.040 --> 01:16:39.360
And I said, my God, what the heck happened there?

01:16:39.980 --> 01:16:41.640
My wife and I were like, that's crazy.

01:16:42.560 --> 01:16:45.680
Clearly someone's going to call the police and tell them that a boat exploded.

01:16:46.140 --> 01:16:47.000
You know, we're on the beach.

01:16:47.060 --> 01:16:48.480
We didn't have phones or anything at the time.

01:16:49.320 --> 01:16:50.120
Like, what the heck is that?

01:16:50.120 --> 01:16:58.280
So I would say five minutes later, wasn't that long, maybe 10 minutes, we see one of

01:16:58.280 --> 01:17:00.200
the helicopters from the Air Force base go out to it.

01:17:00.740 --> 01:17:03.820
So they get up and they fly over it and they hover right over it.

01:17:03.840 --> 01:17:04.380
It's still blinking.

01:17:04.800 --> 01:17:06.140
It's not exploding.

01:17:06.260 --> 01:17:06.720
It's still there.

01:17:06.940 --> 01:17:07.460
Still blinking.

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:08.980
Just a nice pace.

01:17:09.180 --> 01:17:10.240
Bling, bling, bling.

01:17:11.320 --> 01:17:12.680
Helicopter hangs over, looks at it.

01:17:13.640 --> 01:17:14.360
Doesn't do anything.

01:17:14.480 --> 01:17:15.080
Goes all the way back.

01:17:16.460 --> 01:17:18.220
So like, well, are they going to help the people?

01:17:18.340 --> 01:17:19.520
Are they going to, you know, rescue them?

01:17:19.520 --> 01:17:20.860
Or are they going to do any of that?

01:17:20.920 --> 01:17:21.100
Nothing.

01:17:22.180 --> 01:17:23.020
That is so weird.

01:17:24.240 --> 01:17:25.340
That's when it got fun.

01:17:27.740 --> 01:17:32.040
So now, as we're watching this thing, it's about 10, 15, 20 minutes into it.

01:17:33.160 --> 01:17:33.960
It gets closer.

01:17:34.980 --> 01:17:35.900
It's still blinking.

01:17:36.140 --> 01:17:36.920
It's getting closer.

01:17:37.280 --> 01:17:37.880
It's leaving.

01:17:38.000 --> 01:17:38.400
It's moving.

01:17:39.920 --> 01:17:41.360
And then it gets within a mile.

01:17:42.080 --> 01:17:43.000
So is that three miles?

01:17:43.140 --> 01:17:44.020
Is it two miles?

01:17:44.680 --> 01:17:45.680
It gets to about a half a mile.

01:17:46.620 --> 01:17:48.500
And then somewhere at, I think, about a half a mile.

01:17:48.500 --> 01:17:50.260
Well, it's not one light anymore.

01:17:50.780 --> 01:17:51.820
It's split into six.

01:17:53.420 --> 01:17:55.640
And it's not just getting bright.

01:17:57.420 --> 01:18:01.300
These orange, pinkish lights split, and then they started rotating.

01:18:02.720 --> 01:18:03.940
And they just started rotating.

01:18:04.300 --> 01:18:05.980
Like bicycle spokes on a wheel.

01:18:06.840 --> 01:18:07.860
And they kept getting closer.

01:18:08.220 --> 01:18:09.720
And they would go under the water and come back out.

01:18:09.940 --> 01:18:10.900
Under the water, come back out.

01:18:11.160 --> 01:18:12.300
Under the water, come back out.

01:18:12.300 --> 01:18:14.460
I'm like, this is really weird.

01:18:15.080 --> 01:18:16.360
And they got closer to us.

01:18:16.840 --> 01:18:22.340
So when it got about a quarter of a mile or maybe 1,000 yards out, we're like, okay, we're going to walk up the beach now.

01:18:22.620 --> 01:18:23.280
That's been fun.

01:18:24.620 --> 01:18:25.600
That's a little bit too close.

01:18:26.120 --> 01:18:26.880
It kept following us.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:27.480
It got closer.

01:18:27.940 --> 01:18:28.500
It got closer.

01:18:28.780 --> 01:18:29.380
It got brighter.

01:18:29.860 --> 01:18:30.520
It got brighter.

01:18:30.520 --> 01:18:37.540
And I think it was about when they got about, I wouldn't even be exaggerating if I said 50 yards.

01:18:38.420 --> 01:18:38.660
What?

01:18:38.780 --> 01:18:39.500
That close.

01:18:40.540 --> 01:18:41.860
I started getting a little scared.

01:18:42.500 --> 01:18:44.720
And I know she was getting scared.

01:18:44.720 --> 01:18:58.640
Then, after about 40 minutes of looking at these lights and trying to run from them, but not full-out sprint, but kind of just walking super fast, like 12 blocks, it went out.

01:18:59.980 --> 01:19:01.800
And then we walked home.

01:19:03.260 --> 01:19:09.600
And it was terrifying, but it was not super scary, but it was scary enough.

01:19:10.020 --> 01:19:11.420
Because I didn't know what the heck that was.

01:19:11.700 --> 01:19:12.600
That's wild.

01:19:13.100 --> 01:19:14.200
What year was this?

01:19:14.720 --> 01:19:16.320
Probably 2013.

01:19:17.500 --> 01:19:18.040
Somewhere in there.

01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:23.240
So you had already started your work on the more exotic propulsion stuff.

01:19:23.840 --> 01:19:24.700
Probably, yeah.

01:19:24.760 --> 01:19:26.720
A couple years in by then, for sure.

01:19:26.980 --> 01:19:27.960
That's fascinating.

01:19:28.120 --> 01:19:29.080
It's so interesting.

01:19:29.260 --> 01:19:40.020
So you saw this thing out in the distance, and then it started to loop in and out of the water and approach you, and it got to like 50 yards-ish away.

01:19:40.320 --> 01:19:41.420
Yeah, it got really close.

01:19:41.480 --> 01:19:43.680
Beyond the waves, like where the waves started.

01:19:43.680 --> 01:19:48.700
Did it still look like this amorphous light at 50 yards, or could you make out the structure?

01:19:48.900 --> 01:19:49.960
There's no, I couldn't see a structure.

01:19:50.200 --> 01:19:57.100
Just six or seven lights going in a pattern, faster, slower, faster, slower, in and out of the water, like the water wasn't there.

01:19:57.100 --> 01:20:00.280
And just, it was responding to us.

01:20:00.880 --> 01:20:01.280
Really?

01:20:01.280 --> 01:20:01.600
Really?

01:20:02.400 --> 01:20:06.680
Why, so why, because that's a common thing for people to say who've had UFO experiences.

01:20:06.680 --> 01:20:08.240
It just, if we went up, it went up.

01:20:08.360 --> 01:20:11.160
If we went faster, it went faster.

01:20:11.360 --> 01:20:12.240
It was mirroring you.

01:20:12.240 --> 01:20:13.000
It was mirroring us.

01:20:13.000 --> 01:20:20.640
Did you get any sort of consciousness download, or feel mentally locked in with it, or anything like that?

01:20:20.720 --> 01:20:21.020
No.

01:20:22.020 --> 01:20:22.820
No, I don't think so.

